translated: Eriksson, Karl Harry Linné, a civil engineer in road and water construction, lived in Linköping. He was born on February 17, 1906, in Norrköping and married Phæbe Hülphers in 1933. They had two children, Birgitta (born in 1937) and Christer (born in 1939). Eriksson attended Realskolan and then the Engineering School in Norrköping, graduating in 1923 and receiving his engineering degree in 1926. He took various specialist courses before becoming an engineer at the Road and Water Construction District in Norrköping in 1927. From 1927 to 1933, he worked for the construction company Byggn. A-B Paul Anderson in Västerås. From 1933 to 1935, he was a road construction assistant in Västmanland County. From 1935 to 1944, he worked as a consultant engineer in road, bridge, and building construction in Västerås. From 1938 to 1944, he was appointed by the Road and Water Construction Board to oversee contracts for road surfacing and bridge construction in Västmanland County. From 1944 to 1945, he worked as a department engineer for building operations at the Road Administration in Östergötland County and as a lecturer at a technical institute in Stockholm. From 1945 to 1946, he was a road engineer for the Road and Water Construction District with a placement in Östergötland County, and from 1946 until retirement, he worked as a road and water construction engineer with a placement in Östergötland County. His hobby was philosophy.
